      • setBootClasspathProperties

        @NonNull
public ClassPathProviderImpl.Builder setBootClasspathProperties(@NonNull
                                                                         String... bootClasspathProperties)
        Sets boot classpath properties. Some project types do not use JavaPlatform.getBootstrapLibraries() as boot classpath but have a project property specifying the boot classpath. Setting the boot classpath properties causes that the Project's boot classpath is not taken from Project's JavaPlatform but from these properties.
        Parameters:
        bootClasspathProperties - the names of properties containing the boot classpath
        Returns:
        ClassPathProviderImpl.Builder
        Since:
        1.67
